BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, April 3 (KCNA) -- Papers here today 
dedicate by-lined articles to the 10th anniversary of the 
proclamation of the second Republic of Guinea. 
  Since the proclamation of the second Republic, the Guinean 
people have actively striven to carve out their destiny with 
their own efforts, NODONG SINMUN says, and goes on: 
  The Guinean Government and people are making their efforts 
to 
apply the principle of self-reliance in building a new life. 
The Guinean Government is internally directing its attention to 
achieving political stability and unity of the country and 
externally striving to strengthen and develop the non-aligned 
movement. 
  The Korean people are sincerely rejoiced over the 
achievements made by the Guinean people in building a new Guinea. 
  Believing that the friendly and cooperative relations 
between 
the two peoples will further strengthen and develop in various 
fields on the basis of the idea of independence, peace and 
friendship, the Korean people wish the Guinean people greater 
success in their struggle for the development and prosperity of 
the country, says MINJU CHOSON. 

